TLDR: You should use the `org.jpmml.model.jackson.JacksonUtil` utility class for reading and writing JPMML class model objects in JSON data format. Its part of the JPMML-Model library (`org.jpmml:pmml-model-jackson` module).

Where did you get your JSON fragment from? Crafted manually? It doesn&#39;t match the annotations that are present in the `DefineFunction` class.

Writing a dummy `DefineFunction` object into a JSON file:

    DefineFunction defineFunction = new DefineFunction()
	  .addParameterFields(new ParameterField())
	  .setExpression(new MapValues());

    try(OutputStream os = new FileOutputStream(&quot;df.json&quot;){
      JacksonUtil.write(defineFunction, os);
    }

Therefore, the correct JSON structure should look like this:

    {
      &quot;DefineFunction&quot; : {
        &quot;ParameterField&quot; : [ { } ],
        &quot;Expression&quot; : {
          &quot;MapValues&quot; : { }
        }
      }
    }

A correct JSON file reads successfully:

    try(InputStream is = new FileInputStream(&quot;df.json&quot;){
      DefineFunction defineFunction = JacksonUtil.read(DefineFunction.class, is);
    }

